<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10259980>
    dc:description "Fig. 1.—An adult female Eptesicus innoxius from Cerro Cacharí, near Babahoyo, Los Ríos, Ecuador. Photograph by JAS." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10259980/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10259984>
    dc:description "Fig. 2.—Dorsal, ventral, and lateral views of the skull and lateral view of mandible of an adult male Eptesicus innoxius (MZUGM [Museo de Zoología de la Universidad de Guayaquil] 0699) from Cerro El Muerto, Guayaquil, Guayas Province, Ecuador. Greatest length of skull is 14.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10259984/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10259986>
    dc:description "Fig. 3.—Geographic distribution of Eptesicus innoxius redrawn by Christian Loaiza from Loaiza et al. (2020). Arabic numbers correspond to provinces in Ecuador: 1) Esmeraldas, 2) Santo Domingo de los Tsáchilas, 3) Manabí, 4) Los Ríos, 5) Guayas, 6) Santa Elena, 7) El Oro, 8) Loja; and Peru departments: 9) Tumbes, 10) Piura, 11) Lambayeque. The gray shading refers to Andes Mountains." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10259986/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

